WEBVTT

00:00.501 --> 00:02.368
<i> PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i> "SECRETS AND LIES"...</i>

00:02.369 --> 00:04.236
Ben: MY FLASHLIGHT CAME BACK.
Dave: DO YOU EVEN KNOW

00:04.237 --> 00:06.104
IF THE FLASHLIGHT
IS THE MURDER WEAPON?
IT IS.

00:06.707 --> 00:08.340
WHY DO YOU HAVE
THE PREGNANCY TEST?

00:08.342 --> 00:09.641
I'VE NEVER
CHEATED ON YOU.

00:09.643 --> 00:11.176
WHOSE IS IT?
PROCESS OF ELIMINATION.

00:11.178 --> 00:14.013
IT'S NOT CHRISTY'S.
IT'S NOT ABBY'S.

00:14.015 --> 00:15.381
OKAY.
NO!

00:15.383 --> 00:18.017
YOU COME NEAR MY DAUGHTER AGAIN,
AND I WILL KILL YOU.

00:18.019 --> 00:19.018
I HATE YOU.

00:19.020 --> 00:20.185
THAT'S ENOUGH.
LITTLE DRUNK.

00:20.187 --> 00:21.687
[ Yawning ]
WHAT UP, G?

00:21.689 --> 00:23.522
IT'S NOT WHAT YOU THINK,
ALL RIGHT?

00:23.524 --> 00:25.124
YOU'RE MAKING
A REALLY BIG MISTAKE HERE.

00:25.126 --> 00:27.292
BIGGEST MISTAKE I EVER MADE
WAS HAVING YOU FOR A FRIEND!

00:27.294 --> 00:29.361
YOU NEED A RIDE,
MR. LINDSEY?

00:34.301 --> 00:36.635
Shaw:<i> THE BOY LIVED</i>
<i>ON A DEAD-END STREET,</i>

00:36.637 --> 00:38.270
<i> NO FORCED ENTRY,</i>

00:38.272 --> 00:40.172
<i>KILLED NOT FAR FROM HOME,</i>
<i>WITH BOOTS AND JACKET ON.</i>

00:40.174 --> 00:42.174
<i>THINK A 5-YEAR-OLD LEFT</i>
<i>IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT,</i>

00:42.176 --> 00:45.044
<i>WITHOUT MAKING A SOUND,</i>
<i>WITH SOMEONE HE DIDN'T TRUST?</i>

00:45.046 --> 00:47.446
<i>YOU'VE PROFILED CASES LIKE THIS</i>
<i> BEFORE AT THE FBI.</i>

00:47.448 --> 00:49.281
<i> WHAT POSSIBLE MOTIVE</i>
<i> COULD ANYONE HAVE</i>

00:49.283 --> 00:50.616
<i> FOR KILLING</i>
<i> THIS YOUNG BOY?</i>

00:50.618 --> 00:52.785
<i> JEALOUSY OR SEX.</i>

00:52.787 --> 00:55.054
<i> REALLY?</i>
<i> OVER A 5-YEAR-OLD?</i>

00:55.056 --> 00:57.189
<i> ABOUT HALF</i>
<i>OF CHILD-ABDUCTION HOMICIDES</i>

00:57.191 --> 00:58.791
<i> TURN OUT TO BE</i>
<i> SEXUALLY MOTIVATED.</i>

00:58.793 --> 01:01.527
<i>PEDOPHILES AVOID DETECTION</i>
<i> BY APPEARING NORMAL.</i>

01:01.529 --> 01:05.330
<i>THEY'RE YOUR BABYSITTER,</i>
<i>TEACHER, NEXT-DOOR NEIGHBOR.</i>

01:05.332 --> 01:06.765
<i> WHY WOULDN'T</i>
<i> POLICE TELL US</i>

01:06.767 --> 01:09.168
<i> IF THERE WAS EVIDENCE</i>
<i> OF SEXUAL ABUSE?</i>

01:09.170 --> 01:11.503
<i> YOU DON'T ALWAYS</i>
<i> FIND TRACE EVIDENCE.</i>

01:11.505 --> 01:14.773
<i>IF TOM MURPHY WAS GROOMED INTO</i>
<i>SEX ACTS BY A FAMILY FRIEND...</i>
WHY ARE YOU WATCHING THAT?

01:14.775 --> 01:16.575
HOW'S NAT?
<i>...NO ONE WOULD EV--</i>

01:16.577 --> 01:18.243
[ TV TURNS OFF ]
I'VE GOT HER PHONE
AND HER LAPTOP.

01:18.245 --> 01:19.928
IF SHE WON'T TALK TO US,

01:19.929 --> 01:21.612
SHE DOESN'T GET TO TALK
TO HER FRIENDS.

01:21.615 --> 01:24.750
AS FAR AS I KNOW, SHE HASN'T
TAKEN THE PREGNANCY TEST YET.

01:24.752 --> 01:27.286
WHY AREN'T
YOU RUNNING TODAY?

01:27.288 --> 01:29.221
I'M GONNA GO LATER.
[ SIGHS ]

01:29.223 --> 01:31.090
EVERY TIME
I FOLLOW MY ROUTINE,

01:31.092 --> 01:32.758
CORNELL SHOWS UP
TO PAW THROUGH MY STUFF.

01:34.195 --> 01:35.527
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

01:35.529 --> 01:36.728
I'LL GET IT.

01:43.571 --> 01:44.736
READY?

01:44.738 --> 01:46.505
YEAH.
Ben: FOR WHAT?

01:46.507 --> 01:48.841
TAKING MY SISTER
TO BREAKFAST.

01:48.843 --> 01:51.376
IS THIS WHY
YOU'RE RUSHING ME OUT?

01:51.378 --> 01:52.878
Abby: MOM!

01:52.880 --> 01:54.880
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

01:54.882 --> 01:57.850
WHERE'S
THE HAIR DRYER?

01:59.854 --> 02:02.121
SO,
HOW YOU HOLDING UP?

02:02.123 --> 02:04.006
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

02:04.007 --> 02:05.890
BEEN HARD ON CHRISTY
AND THE GIRLS.

02:05.893 --> 02:08.127
WHAT'S WORSE,
THEY COULD LOSE EVERYTHING.

02:08.129 --> 02:10.162
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?
WELL, A CIVIL SUIT

02:10.164 --> 02:12.764
USUALLY FOLLOWS
A CRIMINAL INVESTIGATION.

02:12.766 --> 02:15.134
THIS IS
NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

02:15.136 --> 02:17.202
I CAN TAKE CARE OF MY FAMILY
JUST FINE.

02:17.204 --> 02:19.538
THEN DO
THE DECENT THING --

02:19.540 --> 02:22.708
PUT YOUR ASSETS IN A TRUST FUND
BEFORE IT'S TOO LATE.

02:22.710 --> 02:25.477
YOU THINK
I'M GOING TO PRISON?

02:25.479 --> 02:28.147
EVERYBODY THINKS
YOU'RE GOING TO PRISON.

02:35.923 --> 02:39.658
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

02:56.777 --> 02:59.645
[ COE 24K's "A DIFFERENCE"
PLAYING IN DISTANCE ]

02:59.647 --> 03:02.748
¶ A LYRICAL NUISANCE,
DON'T DO NOTHING STUPID ¶

03:02.750 --> 03:05.517
¶ LIKE KILLING YA CAREER,
SAYING SOMETHING FOOLISH ¶

03:05.519 --> 03:08.287
¶ DON'T LET NOTHING SLIP,
IF YOU'RE NOT CONFIDENT ¶

03:08.289 --> 03:09.288
¶ HERE'S SOME INCENTIVE, I -- ¶

03:09.290 --> 03:10.589
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

03:10.591 --> 03:13.825
Vanessa: HOW COULD YOU?!
THIS IS MALCOLM'S!

03:13.827 --> 03:15.294
STOP JUST
DOING THINGS LIKE THIS!

03:15.295 --> 03:16.762
VANESSA, WE HAVE TO TRY TO GET
OVER THIS AT SOME POINT!

03:16.764 --> 03:17.863
HOW DARE YOU!

03:17.865 --> 03:20.399
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

03:20.401 --> 03:23.869
[ SIGHS ]

03:23.871 --> 03:26.438
13 DAYS. YOU'D HAVE THOUGHT
THEY'D MOVED ON BY NOW, EH?

03:26.440 --> 03:28.974
YEAH.

03:28.976 --> 03:30.759
WHAT HAPPENED?

03:30.760 --> 03:32.543
I-I -- I GOT IN THE MIDDLE
OF SOMETHING.

03:32.546 --> 03:34.880
DIDN'T WORK OUT TOO WELL
BY THE LOOKS OF IT.

03:34.882 --> 03:36.615
WHY DON'T YOU
DROP BY THE OFFICE?

03:36.617 --> 03:37.916
I'LL FIX IT UP
FOR YOU.

03:37.918 --> 03:40.419
OKAY, I'LL COME BY
AFTER WORK.

03:40.421 --> 03:41.753
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

03:41.755 --> 03:43.422
OH, HERE COME
THE VULTURES.

03:43.424 --> 03:44.756
SEE YA.

03:44.758 --> 03:47.226
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

04:00.874 --> 04:02.608
[ SIGHS ]

04:06.814 --> 04:09.681
NAT...

04:09.683 --> 04:11.350
I'M AN IDIOT.

04:11.352 --> 04:13.852
THE FIRST THING
I SHOULD HAVE SAID IS,

04:13.854 --> 04:17.522
IT'S GONNA BE OKAY, THAT
YOUR MOTHER AND I LOVE YOU...

04:17.524 --> 04:19.891
THAT WE'LL BELIEVE
WHATEVER YOU TELL US.

04:24.832 --> 04:26.031
OKAY.

04:29.803 --> 04:32.271
HONEY,
IF DAVE TOUCHED YOU...

04:32.273 --> 04:33.272
[ SCOFFS ]

04:33.274 --> 04:35.774
...I NEED TO KNOW!
NAT!

04:35.776 --> 04:37.860
NATALIE!

04:37.861 --> 04:39.945
AT THIS RATE, YOU'RE GONNA
RUN OUT OF PEOPLE TO ACCUSE.

04:39.947 --> 04:41.680
DAVE'S A JACKASS,
NOT A PERVERT.
[ BEEP ]

04:41.682 --> 04:43.649
I KNOW WHAT I SAW.

04:43.651 --> 04:44.783
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

04:44.785 --> 04:46.685
YOU'VE KNOWN HIM
SINCE HIGH SCHOOL.

04:46.687 --> 04:48.287
PEOPLE CHANGE.

04:48.289 --> 04:50.989
SO, HE DID IT,
JUST LIKE THAT?

04:50.991 --> 04:52.491
[ SIGHS ]

04:52.493 --> 04:55.060
MRS. CRAWFORD.

04:55.062 --> 04:56.461
I WAS JUST STARTING
TO MISS YOU.

04:56.463 --> 04:59.865
SHAME,
I'M NOT HERE FOR YOU.

04:59.867 --> 05:01.867
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

05:01.869 --> 05:02.868
Natalie: GO AWAY.

05:02.870 --> 05:04.569
THERE'S SOMEONE HERE
TO SEE YOU.

05:04.571 --> 05:06.571
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

05:06.573 --> 05:07.739
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

05:09.977 --> 05:12.878
HI, NATALIE.
CAN WE TALK?

05:14.915 --> 05:16.515
OKAY.

05:21.522 --> 05:22.988
DO THEY
HAVE TO BE HERE?

05:22.990 --> 05:25.991
YOU'RE A MINOR,
SO, YES, THEY DO.

05:25.993 --> 05:29.027
NOW, WHERE WERE YOU TWO NIGHTS
BEFORE TOM MURPHY WAS KILLED?

05:29.029 --> 05:30.028
WHY DOES THAT MATTER?

05:30.030 --> 05:32.898
EVERYTHING MATTERS.

05:32.900 --> 05:34.566
TOM'S MURDER
WAS PREMEDITATED,

05:34.568 --> 05:36.568
SO I NEED TO KNOW
WHO HAD ACCESS TO HIM,

05:36.570 --> 05:39.671
WHEN THEY HAD IT,
AND HOW OFTEN.

05:41.008 --> 05:43.041
IT'S A SIMPLE QUESTION.

05:43.043 --> 05:45.544
WERE YOU BABY-SITTING TOM
THAT NIGHT?

05:45.546 --> 05:47.412
OF COURSE SHE WAS.
REALLY?

05:49.616 --> 05:53.618
ACTUALLY, SHE WASN'T.
RIGHT?

05:53.620 --> 05:56.038
NOW, AS I SAID
TO YOUR PARENTS,

05:56.039 --> 05:58.457
YOU CAN ANSWER QUESTIONS HERE
OR GO DOWNTOWN WITH ME.

06:03.931 --> 06:06.064
IT'S NOT LIKE
I ABANDONED TOM.

06:06.066 --> 06:07.599
VANESSA
WAS WATCHING HIM.

06:07.601 --> 06:09.768
MRS. RICHARDSON.
WHAT?

06:09.770 --> 06:11.603
WHERE THE HELL
WERE YOU?!

06:11.605 --> 06:13.438
AFTER TOM
FELL ASLEEP...

06:13.440 --> 06:17.909
VANESSA CAME OVER TO WATCH HIM
SO I COULD GO TO A CONCERT

06:17.911 --> 06:19.778
WITH COOPER.

06:19.780 --> 06:21.913
[ SIGHS ]
[ SIGHS ]

06:23.851 --> 06:25.517
SATISFIED, DETECTIVE?

06:25.519 --> 06:27.853
ABSOLUTELY.

06:35.763 --> 06:37.429
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

06:37.431 --> 06:38.764
Man:
DETECTIVE, ANY STATEMENT?

06:38.766 --> 06:40.132
[ DOOR CLOSES ]
HELP US OUT HERE!

06:40.134 --> 06:41.666
YEAH, WE'RE STILL WAITING.

06:41.668 --> 06:42.934
WHAT DID NAT SAY?

06:42.936 --> 06:44.936
[ SIGHS ]
SHE APOLOGIZED FOR EVERYTHING.

06:44.938 --> 06:46.605
SHE DIDN'T SAY
A DAMN THING.

06:46.607 --> 06:49.441
CLAMMED UP THE MINUTE
CORNELL WALKED OUT.

06:49.443 --> 06:52.778
DO YOU THINK...
IS NAT A SUSPECT?

06:52.780 --> 06:54.313
NO.

06:54.314 --> 06:55.847
I'M PRETTY SURE CORNELL'S
JUST SCREWING WITH ME.

06:55.849 --> 06:56.948
AGAIN.

06:56.950 --> 06:58.884
WHAT?
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

06:58.885 --> 07:00.819
I'M GONNA FIND OUT WHAT ELSE
OUR DAUGHTER LIED ABOUT.

07:00.821 --> 07:01.987
Woman: SCOTT MURPHY'S
BEEN CLEARED

07:01.989 --> 07:03.855
BY POLICE FOR TOM'S MURDER.
HAVE YOU?

07:03.857 --> 07:05.724
Man: WHY DID THEY QUESTION
YOUR FRIEND DAVE?

07:05.726 --> 07:06.892
WHAT CAN YOU TELL US,
BEN?

07:06.894 --> 07:10.028
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

07:10.030 --> 07:11.596
HEY, BEN! COME ON!

07:15.002 --> 07:16.902
[ DOORBELL RINGING ]

07:24.812 --> 07:26.845
BEN?
HEY.

07:26.847 --> 07:28.747
WE NEED TO TALK.

07:28.749 --> 07:31.583
YOU KNOW, IT IS HARD ENOUGH
RAISING A TEENAGER

07:31.585 --> 07:34.653
WITHOUT YOUR NEIGHBORS
COVERING FOR THEM.

07:34.655 --> 07:38.056
YOU WATCHED TOM SO NATALIE
COULD SNEAK OFF TO A CONCERT.

07:38.058 --> 07:41.059
OH, I'M SORRY.
I-I THOUGHT YOU KNEW.

07:42.596 --> 07:44.930
NEXT TIME,
CHECK WITH US FIRST.

07:44.932 --> 07:47.132
THERE WON'T BE
A NEXT TIME.

07:50.871 --> 07:53.538
ARE YOU OKAY?

07:53.540 --> 07:56.842
JUST PEACHY.

07:56.844 --> 07:58.543
YOU?

08:02.950 --> 08:06.585
THAT WAS
AT TOM'S SHRINE.

08:06.587 --> 08:09.754
IT DIDN'T BELONG THERE.

08:09.756 --> 08:10.889
[ SNIFFLES ]

08:10.891 --> 08:12.958
IT WAS OUR SON,
MALCOLM'S.

08:12.960 --> 08:16.261
I...DIDN'T KNOW
YOU HAD A SON.

08:19.733 --> 08:22.901
TODAY IS HIS BIRTHDAY.

08:22.903 --> 08:24.936
HE WAS TAKEN FROM US.

08:27.140 --> 08:29.007
I'M SORRY.

08:29.009 --> 08:31.576
WOULD YOU LIKE
TO SEE MALCOLM?

08:42.623 --> 08:44.990
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:47.794 --> 08:49.794
[ SNIFFLES ]
I NEED ANOTHER.

08:49.796 --> 08:50.996
WOULD YOU LIKE ONE?

08:50.998 --> 08:52.898
UH, NO, I'M OKAY.

08:56.103 --> 08:58.537
[ REFRIGERATOR DOOR OPENS ]

09:03.110 --> 09:05.877
[ ICE CLINKING ]

09:07.915 --> 09:10.015
[ GLASSES CLINKING ]

09:10.017 --> 09:11.983
[ LIQUID POURING ]

09:14.087 --> 09:16.955
VANESSA, I THINK I WILL
HAVE THAT DRINK.

09:16.957 --> 09:18.690
OKAY.

09:20.861 --> 09:22.661
[ BEEPING ]

09:24.865 --> 09:26.765
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

09:31.972 --> 09:33.204
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

09:44.751 --> 09:46.618
YOU SAID
WE WERE GONNA PAINT.

09:46.620 --> 09:48.136
WE ARE.

09:48.137 --> 09:49.653
JUST A QUICK STOP
AT DR. RICHARDSON'S.

09:49.656 --> 09:51.289
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE OKAY.

09:51.291 --> 09:53.291
I AM. HE JUST WANTS TO
TREAT MY CUT RIGHT AWAY

09:53.293 --> 09:54.960
SO IT HEALS FASTER.

09:54.962 --> 09:56.294
[ CHILDREN LAUGHING ]

09:56.296 --> 09:58.196
ALL RIGHT. YEAH.

10:01.335 --> 10:05.036
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

10:05.038 --> 10:06.871
YOU'RE PROBABLY
THE OLDEST PATIENT

10:06.873 --> 10:08.840
DR. RICHARDSON'S
EVER HAD.

10:08.842 --> 10:10.141
PROBABLY.

10:10.143 --> 10:12.143
YOU DON'T
NEED TO BE NERVOUS.

10:12.145 --> 10:13.845
YOU JUST HAVE TO
HOLD STILL.

10:13.847 --> 10:15.680
Ben: ALL RIGHT, BIG BOY,
HOLD STILL.

10:16.750 --> 10:18.850
HOLD STILL, AND...

10:18.852 --> 10:21.186
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]
...NICE!

10:21.188 --> 10:23.855
THE FISH IS A KEEPER.
I'M NOT SURE ABOUT THE PICTURE.

10:23.857 --> 10:25.991
LET ME GET HIM
OFF THE LINE HERE.

10:28.895 --> 10:31.329
WHAT HAPPENS
IF WE DON'T PUT HIM BACK?

10:31.331 --> 10:32.864
WELL, HE'LL DIE.

10:32.866 --> 10:34.833
WILL HE
GO TO HEAVEN?

10:34.835 --> 10:35.934
NO, SILLY!
IT'S DINNER!

10:35.936 --> 10:37.369
HEY, ABBY,
CAREFUL THERE!

10:37.371 --> 10:38.903
IF YOU FELL IN,
THAT CURRENT'S STRONG.

10:38.905 --> 10:41.006
Natalie:
IT COULD WASH YOU AWAY.

10:41.008 --> 10:43.742
HEY --
HE'S NOT READY
TO BE DEAD.

10:48.915 --> 10:51.950
Man: ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT, THAT'S GOOD.

10:51.952 --> 10:53.218
WELL, NO FLOATERS.

10:53.220 --> 10:56.054
NO SIGN OF CONCUSSION,
BUT I'M GLAD YOU CAME IN.

10:58.158 --> 11:01.393
DO YOU THINK --
I-I SAW ON THE NEWS --

11:01.395 --> 11:03.395
IT COULD HAVE BEEN A NEIGHBOR
THAT KILLED TOM?

11:03.397 --> 11:04.663
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:04.665 --> 11:06.965
WELL...

11:06.967 --> 11:08.967
THE PRESS KNOW EVEN LESS
THAN THE POLICE DO.

11:08.969 --> 11:11.369
THEY JUST MAKE THINGS UP
AS THEY GO ALONG...

11:13.440 --> 11:18.076
...HURTING INNOCENT PEOPLE,
RUINING LIVES.

11:23.050 --> 11:25.083
DID YOU KNOW
TOM WAS YOURS?

11:26.687 --> 11:28.153
I'M SORRY.

11:28.155 --> 11:30.455
UM, I HAVE NO BUSINESS
ASKING THAT QUESTION.

11:30.457 --> 11:32.057
IT'S OKAY.

11:33.827 --> 11:35.827
I DIDN'T...

11:35.829 --> 11:38.129
UNTIL AFTER.

11:38.131 --> 11:41.800
IT MUST HAVE BEEN
DEVASTATING.

11:41.802 --> 11:43.935
YOU PROBABLY
HAVE SOME IDEA.

11:43.937 --> 11:46.304
I MEAN, AFTER MALCOLM
WAS TAKEN FROM YOU.

11:47.874 --> 11:51.042
VANESSA TOLD ME.

11:51.044 --> 11:55.046
MALCOLM WASN'T TAKEN,
BEN.

11:55.048 --> 11:56.981
HE DIED.

11:56.983 --> 12:00.852
I'M SORRY.

12:06.993 --> 12:08.493
I WISH
I COULD TELL YOU

12:08.495 --> 12:12.497
THAT THE PAIN OF LOSING A CHILD
GOES AWAY...

12:12.499 --> 12:14.733
BUT IT DOESN'T.

12:14.735 --> 12:16.034
VANESSA AND I

12:16.036 --> 12:18.169
JUST HAVE DIFFERENT WAYS
OF DEALING WITH IT.

12:18.171 --> 12:21.506
SO,<i> YOU</i> PUT THE BUNNY
AT TOM'S SHRINE?

12:21.508 --> 12:24.342
LEAVING IT FOR TOM
MADE SENSE TO ME --

12:24.344 --> 12:26.911
ANOTHER STEP
TOWARDS LETTING GO.

12:26.913 --> 12:29.948
BUT VANESSA'S
NOT READY.

12:32.819 --> 12:35.453
YOU'RE A SOCCER FAN,
HUH?

12:36.957 --> 12:39.124
NO, BEN. THAT...

12:39.126 --> 12:40.825
IS FOOTBALL.

12:40.827 --> 12:42.527
RIGHT.

12:45.031 --> 12:48.032
ALL RIGHT,
STEADY, STEADY.

12:48.034 --> 12:50.118
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

12:50.119 --> 12:52.203
NO, NO, THAT WASN'T
THE DEAL, CHLOE.

12:52.205 --> 12:54.973
I GAVE YOU CHRISTMAS DAY
SO THAT I COULD HAVE --

12:54.975 --> 12:58.009
THAT'S GOOD, THAT'S GOOD.
FINE. FINE.

12:58.011 --> 13:00.044
JUST LIKE --
I'M GONNA LET GO.

13:00.046 --> 13:02.530
ALL RIGHT,
YOU'RE ON YOUR OWN.

13:02.531 --> 13:05.015
ABBY. ABBY, I'VE GOT SOME SNACKS
OUT FRONT IF YOU'RE INTERESTED.

13:06.119 --> 13:08.570
GO ON.

13:08.571 --> 13:11.022
NO -- BUT -- NO,
BUT THAT'S NOT...

13:11.024 --> 13:12.490
WHAT...HAPPENED.

13:12.492 --> 13:14.859
Y-- CHLOE.

13:14.861 --> 13:15.994
CHLOE.

13:17.397 --> 13:19.397
FINE. FINE!

13:19.399 --> 13:20.899
[ BEEP ]

13:20.901 --> 13:22.567
[ SIGHS ]

13:22.569 --> 13:25.820
GUESS I'LL BE GOING
BACK TO FAMILY COURT.

13:25.821 --> 13:29.072
MAN, NO DOUBT MY EX WILL
LIE HER ASS OFF TO WIN CUSTODY.

13:29.075 --> 13:32.577
AND WHO WILL SUFFER?
MY KIDS, MY REPUTATION.

13:32.579 --> 13:34.813
GUILTY WHETHER
YOU DID IT OR NOT.

13:34.815 --> 13:36.447
YEAH, WELL, THAT'S WHY
I'M GOING TO COURT --

13:36.449 --> 13:38.349
FIGHT THE GOOD FIGHT.

13:38.351 --> 13:41.052
LOOK, YOU SHOULD
GO TO THE PRESS,

13:41.054 --> 13:43.121
SET THE RECORD
STRAIGHT.

13:43.122 --> 13:45.189
THE PRESS DON'T WANT THE TRUTH.
THEY WANT A GOOD STORY.

13:45.192 --> 13:47.042
THEN GIVE THEM YOURS.

13:47.043 --> 13:48.893
NO ONE KNOWS YOU'RE INNOCENT
UNTIL YOU TELL THEM.

13:48.895 --> 13:51.062
Abby:
THE POLICE DO.

13:51.064 --> 13:53.031
MY DAD TOOK A LIE-DETECTOR TEST
TO PROVE IT.

13:53.033 --> 13:55.033
HE DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

13:55.035 --> 13:57.368
WELL, GOOD FOR YOU,
STICKING UP FOR YOUR OLD MAN.

13:57.370 --> 13:58.937
SOMEONE HAS TO.

13:58.939 --> 14:00.972
EVERYWHERE WE GO,
PEOPLE STARE AT US -- SO MEAN.

14:00.974 --> 14:04.008
OKAY, ABBY,
MR. FENTON'S A BUSY MAN.

14:04.010 --> 14:05.610
HE'S GOT WORK TO DO.

14:05.612 --> 14:09.013
AND SO DO YOU, MISSY.
COME ON.

14:18.291 --> 14:21.192
HOW DID YOU KNOW
ABOUT THE LIE-DETECTOR TEST?

14:22.629 --> 14:24.996
I HEARD YOU AND MOM.
ABBY...

14:24.998 --> 14:26.731
I KNOW.

14:26.732 --> 14:28.465
I SHOULDN'T LISTEN TO
OTHER PEOPLE'S CONVERSATIONS.

14:28.468 --> 14:30.468
AND REPEATING IT,
ESPECIALLY TO STRANGERS,

14:30.470 --> 14:31.970
THAT'S WORSE.

14:31.972 --> 14:34.072
I JUST WANT EVERYONE
TO KNOW THE TRUTH, DADDY.

14:34.074 --> 14:35.206
YOU DIDN'T KILL TOM.

14:35.208 --> 14:36.908
THEY WILL, MONKEY.

14:36.910 --> 14:38.910
SOON ENOUGH.

14:38.912 --> 14:40.979
BUT SOME THINGS
YOU JUST DON'T REPEAT, OKAY?

14:45.952 --> 14:48.186
[ CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING ]

14:49.956 --> 14:53.124
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

14:53.126 --> 14:55.460
MOM, DID YOU
GET THE TICKETS?

14:55.462 --> 14:57.395
Christy:
WE'LL GET THEM THERE!

14:57.397 --> 14:58.563
SURE YOU DON'T
WANT TO COME, DAD?

14:58.565 --> 15:00.031
NAH, YOU AND MOM GO.

15:00.033 --> 15:02.100
HAVE A GIRLS' NIGHT.

15:02.102 --> 15:04.235
NAT'S STILL UP THERE?

15:04.237 --> 15:06.237
YEAH,
LOCKED IN HER ROOM.

15:06.239 --> 15:07.906
HOW MANY MORE YEARS
OF TEENAGERS DO WE HAVE?

15:07.908 --> 15:09.975
MM.

15:09.976 --> 15:12.043
I DON'T EVEN WANT TO THINK ABOUT
WHAT THIS ONE'S GONNA BE LIKE.

15:12.045 --> 15:14.379
HEY. I'M THE GOOD ONE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:14.381 --> 15:16.614
I DON'T HAVE SEX
OR SNEAK COOPER INTO MY ROOM

15:16.616 --> 15:19.217
OR DRINK BEER WITH MY STUPID
FRIENDS IN THE WOODS.

15:20.587 --> 15:22.086
THAT WAS BEFORE...

15:22.088 --> 15:24.122
WHEN SHE...

15:24.124 --> 15:28.092
YEAH, NEVER MIND.
LET'S GET GOING.

15:28.094 --> 15:30.328
HAVE FUN.

15:39.706 --> 15:41.105
[ BEEP ]

16:11.004 --> 16:14.172
[ SCOFFS ]

16:49.009 --> 16:52.477
Hardwicke:
<i>I TOOK YOUR CALL BECAUSE</i>
<i>YOUR STORY'S GAINING MOMENTUM,</i>

16:52.479 --> 16:54.112
<i>EVEN ACROSS THE POND HERE,</i>

16:54.114 --> 16:57.448
<i>AND I AM SURE THAT</i> THE GUARDIAN
<i>WOULD BE VERY INTERESTED</i>

16:57.450 --> 16:59.617
<i>IN HEARING WHATEVER IT IS</i>
<i>THAT YOU HAVE TO SAY.</i>

16:59.619 --> 17:01.619
UH, YEAH, NO COMMENT.

17:01.621 --> 17:02.754
<i> I'M NOT REALLY</i>
<i> IN THE HABIT</i>

17:02.756 --> 17:05.289
<i>OF SHARING MY RESEARCH</i>
<i> WITH MY PEERS.</i>

17:05.291 --> 17:08.026
<i>MR. CRAWFORD, I'M SURE YOU'LL</i>
<i>AGREE THAT'S BAD BUSINESS.</i>

17:08.028 --> 17:11.496
I'M NOT A PEER.
I'M A WORRIED FATHER.

17:11.498 --> 17:15.333
MR. HARDWICKE, PLEASE...

17:15.335 --> 17:19.037
YOUR ARTICLES SAY HE WAS FIRED
FOR SEXUAL MISCONDUCT,

17:19.039 --> 17:21.739
BUT YOU NEVER SAY EXACTLY
WHAT DR. RAWLINGS DID.

17:21.741 --> 17:26.611
<i>I DIDN'T SPECIFY THE NATURE</i>
<i>OF THE SEXUAL MISCONDUCT</i>

17:26.613 --> 17:29.580
<i> BECAUSE...</i>
<i> I DIDN'T KNOW IT.</i>

17:29.582 --> 17:33.084
<i>HE WAS SACKED AFTER A CLOSED</i>
<i>HEARING IN FAMILY COURT.</i>

17:33.086 --> 17:35.586
<i>MAGISTRATES ORDERED</i>
<i>THE RECORD SEALED.</i>

17:35.588 --> 17:37.121
IS THAT UNUSUAL?

17:37.123 --> 17:40.124
<i>ACTUALLY, IT'S MANDATORY</i>
<i>IN CERTAIN SENSITIVE CASES.</i>

17:40.126 --> 17:43.061
CASES
INVOLVING CHILDREN.

17:43.063 --> 17:45.563
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE
YOU CAN REMEMBER?

17:45.565 --> 17:49.367
RUMOR WAS, WHATEVER IT WAS
RAWLINGS WAS INTO,

17:49.369 --> 17:51.402
SO WAS HIS WIFE.

17:56.843 --> 17:59.510
Ben: THEIR SOCIAL SERVICES
GOT INVOLVED.

17:59.512 --> 18:03.114
THERE'S ONLY ONE REASON
THEY SEAL THE RECORD --

18:03.116 --> 18:04.782
IT'S CHILD SEXUAL ABUSE.

18:04.784 --> 18:08.252
SO YOU THINK THE DOCTOR
ABUSED KIDS OVERSEAS?

18:08.254 --> 18:11.122
I-I THINK HIS WIFE
MIGHT BE INVOLVED, TOO.

18:11.124 --> 18:13.791
I'M GONNA
CONTACT THE BRITS,

18:13.793 --> 18:15.460
PULL THE SEALED FILES
OFF THE SYSTEM.

18:15.462 --> 18:17.161
YOU NEED ANYTHING?

18:17.163 --> 18:19.831
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

18:19.833 --> 18:21.199
[ SIGHS ]

18:21.201 --> 18:24.769
YOU TRYING
TO GO AROUND ME?

18:24.771 --> 18:26.604
[ SIGHS ]

18:26.606 --> 18:29.307
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

18:29.309 --> 18:32.810
I WAS HOPING SOMEONE IN SEX
CRIMES MIGHT ACTUALLY LISTEN.

18:32.812 --> 18:35.646
WELL, YOU HAVE
MY UNDIVIDED ATTENTION.

18:35.648 --> 18:37.648
YEAH,
THAT'S THE PROBLEM.

18:37.650 --> 18:39.150
UH, YOU'RE
SO FOCUSED ON ME,

18:39.152 --> 18:40.785
YOU'RE NOT LOOKING
FOR ANYONE ELSE.

18:40.787 --> 18:43.321
RICHARDSON WAS FIRED
FOR SEXUAL MISCONDUCT.

18:43.323 --> 18:45.156
HIS DEAD SON
WAS BEATEN.

18:45.158 --> 18:47.258
HE MOVES HERE,
HE CHANGES HIS NAME,

18:47.260 --> 18:48.760
AND THEN TOM'S
BEATEN TO DEATH,

18:48.761 --> 18:50.261
AND YOU DON'T THINK
THAT'S WORTH LOOKING INTO?!

18:50.263 --> 18:53.364
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
I HAVEN'T?

18:54.868 --> 18:56.868
I'LL TELL YOU THIS --

18:56.870 --> 18:59.537
THE RECEIPT THAT YOUR WIFE
SO GRACIOUSLY PROVIDED

18:59.539 --> 19:01.956
SHOWS THAT YOUR
MISSING FLASHLIGHT...

19:01.957 --> 19:04.374
[ SIGHS ]
...IS THE EXACT SAME MAKE AND
MODEL AS THE MURDER WEAPON.

19:04.377 --> 19:07.378
UNLESS I'M THE ONLY ONE WHO OWNS
ONE, IT DOESN'T PROVE A THING.

19:07.380 --> 19:10.448
ALL WE WANT
ARE ANSWERS.

19:10.450 --> 19:12.050
YOU'RE GOING AFTER ME.

19:12.051 --> 19:13.651
MEANWHILE, JOE AND VANESSA
ARE LYING ABOUT WHO THEY ARE.

19:13.653 --> 19:15.319
EVERYBODY LIES.

19:15.321 --> 19:18.389
YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT.
NATALIE, FOR INSTANCE.

19:18.391 --> 19:21.159
LEAVE MY DAUGHTER
OUT OF THIS.

19:23.897 --> 19:26.731
HAVE I DONE
SOMETHING TO YOU?

19:26.733 --> 19:29.234
ME? NO.

19:29.235 --> 19:31.736
THIS IS A FRIENDLY CONVERSATION.
YOU'RE FREE TO LEAVE.

19:33.173 --> 19:36.908
[ SIGHS ]
SHE WASN'T WITH COOPER
THE NIGHT OF THE CONCERT.

19:40.246 --> 19:41.746
WHO WAS SHE WITH?

19:41.748 --> 19:44.916
YOU SHOULD ASK
YOUR FRIEND DAVE.

19:44.918 --> 19:47.518
HE'S STILL YOUR FRIEND,
RIGHT?

20:05.438 --> 20:07.438
[ TV CHATTER ]

20:07.440 --> 20:09.273
HEY, MRS. LINDSEY.

20:09.275 --> 20:11.609
25 YEARS, YOU STILL
WON'T CALL ME "ELLIE"?

20:11.611 --> 20:13.277
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

20:13.279 --> 20:15.947
GOD, YOU LOOK AWFUL.

20:15.949 --> 20:17.949
I'M OKAY.

20:17.951 --> 20:20.618
UH, I NEED TO TALK TO DAVE.
IS HE AROUND?

20:20.620 --> 20:21.953
YEAH.

20:21.955 --> 20:23.921
NO SURPRISE
THAT CRYSTAL OF YOURS

20:23.923 --> 20:25.623
AIN'T BEEN TAKING
GOOD CARE OF YOU.

20:25.625 --> 20:27.458
IT'S CHRISTY.

20:27.460 --> 20:29.560
WHATEVER HAPPENED TO KELLY,
THAT ONE YOU USED TO RUN WITH?

20:29.562 --> 20:32.230
ALWAYS LIKED THAT ONE.

20:32.232 --> 20:33.898
I'D RATHER
PASS A GALLSTONE

20:33.900 --> 20:36.834
THAN BELIEVE ANY OF THAT TRASH
THEY'RE SAYING ABOUT YOU ON TV.

20:36.836 --> 20:39.303
[ SIGHS ]

20:42.875 --> 20:44.742
Dave:
WHAT DID I DO NOW?!

20:44.744 --> 20:47.912
YOU HAVE A VISITOR.
HURRY UP.

20:47.914 --> 20:50.982
BEST STAND BACK.

20:50.984 --> 20:53.818
WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH YOU TWO?

20:53.820 --> 20:55.353
WE HAD A FIGHT.

20:55.355 --> 20:56.887
AS IF I COULDN'T HAVE
FIGURED THAT OUT MYSELF.

20:56.889 --> 20:59.590
HE IS AN IDIOT
AND YOU'RE AN IDIOT,

20:59.592 --> 21:01.492
SO MAKES PERFECT SENSE
YOU'RE BEST FRIENDS.

21:01.494 --> 21:03.961
[ DOOR OPENS ]

21:03.963 --> 21:05.796
[ TOILET FLUSHES ]

21:05.798 --> 21:08.833
WHAT, MAN?
YOU WANT TO APOLOGIZE?

21:08.835 --> 21:11.002
NO.

21:11.004 --> 21:13.437
YOU TOOK NATALIE
TO A CONCERT.

21:13.439 --> 21:15.890
NO.

21:15.891 --> 21:18.342
OKAY, SHE ASKED ME TO SCORE HER
TICKETS FOR THE CONCERT.

21:18.344 --> 21:20.678
COOPER FLAKED
AT THE LAST MINUTE.

21:20.680 --> 21:22.013
SHE WAS GONNA GO ALONE,

21:22.014 --> 21:23.347
SO I TOOK HER
'CAUSE I'M LOOKING OUT FOR HER.

21:23.349 --> 21:24.815
OH, LIKE YOU DID
IN MY GUESTHOUSE?

21:24.817 --> 21:27.685
MAN, IF YOU TALKED
TO NATALIE, THEN...

21:27.687 --> 21:28.853
YOU KNOW
ABOUT THE CONCERT

21:28.855 --> 21:30.672
AND YOU KNOW
THAT NOTHING HAPPENED.

21:30.673 --> 21:32.490
<i> CORNELL</i> TOLD ME
ABOUT THE CONCERT,

21:32.492 --> 21:34.592
AND I CAME HERE TO SEE
WHAT ELSE YOU TOLD HER!

21:34.594 --> 21:36.894
SO I'M A PERVERT
AND A SNITCH AND WHAT ELSE?

21:36.896 --> 21:38.462
DUDE, I'M --
I'M NOT KIDDING!

21:38.464 --> 21:39.930
TELL ME
WHAT YOU TOLD CORNELL!

21:39.932 --> 21:41.332
YOU'RE CRAZY, MAN.

21:41.334 --> 21:42.500
YOU'RE GOING AROUND,

21:42.502 --> 21:43.934
YOU'RE ACCUSING EVERYBODY
LIKE A LUNATIC.

21:43.936 --> 21:46.837
CAN'T YOU SEE
WHAT YOU'RE DOING TO EVERYBODY?

21:46.839 --> 21:51.642
WHAT THE HELL
IS HAPPENING TO YOU?

21:53.613 --> 21:55.913
YOU DON'T GET IT.

21:55.915 --> 21:57.915
YEAH, NO.

21:57.917 --> 21:59.917
HOW CAN I UNDERSTAND
WHAT IT'S LIKE

21:59.919 --> 22:02.987
TO BE ACCUSED
OF SOMETHING I DIDN'T DO?

22:05.858 --> 22:08.859
I HELD NATALIE IN MY ARMS
THE DAY SHE WAS BORN, MAN.

22:08.861 --> 22:11.896
I-I DON'T GET HOW YOU THINK
THAT I COULD EVEN...

22:11.898 --> 22:13.247
DO SOMETHING LIKE THAT
TO HER,

22:13.248 --> 22:14.597
THAT I COULD DO
SOMETHING LIKE THAT TO YOU.

22:14.600 --> 22:16.067
YOU'RE MY --
YOU'RE -- [ SIGHS ]

22:16.069 --> 22:18.102
YOU<i> WERE</i>
MY BEST FRIEND.

22:18.104 --> 22:19.870
YOU WERE MY<i> ONLY</i>
FRIEND.

22:19.872 --> 22:21.806
AND NOW WE'RE DONE.

22:21.808 --> 22:25.676
JUST GET OUT OF HERE,
PLEASE,

22:25.678 --> 22:28.045
BEFORE I REALLY
GET ANGRY.

22:29.716 --> 22:31.716
GET OUT!
GET OUT OF HERE.

22:31.718 --> 22:32.917
JUST GET OUT OF HERE!

22:45.598 --> 22:47.665
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

22:52.538 --> 22:54.605
WHEN WE WERE...

22:56.075 --> 22:59.944
...DID YOU TAKE
A HOME PREGNANCY TEST?

22:59.946 --> 23:01.512
THE FIRST TIME.

23:01.514 --> 23:03.681
THE SECOND TIME,
I JUST...

23:03.683 --> 23:04.882
KNEW.

23:06.819 --> 23:09.520
ARE THEY ACCURATE?
[ SCOFFS ]

23:09.522 --> 23:12.523
OH, THANK GOD I'M NOT THE ONLY
ONE OBSESSING OVER THIS.

23:12.525 --> 23:14.859
[ SIGHS ]

23:14.861 --> 23:16.694
REMEMBER WHEN THEY WERE LITTLE
AND ALL I HAD TO DO

23:16.696 --> 23:18.529
WAS JUST HOLD THEM DOWN
AND MAKE THEM DO IT?

23:18.531 --> 23:20.865
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]
SO EASY THEN.

23:20.867 --> 23:22.500
[ Laughing ] YEAH.

23:22.502 --> 23:26.804
[ SIGHS ] WHY WON'T SHE
JUST GET IT OVER WITH?

23:26.806 --> 23:28.639
PROBABLY BECAUSE

23:28.641 --> 23:32.576
SHE'S AS TERRIFIED
OF THE ANSWER AS WE ARE.

23:32.578 --> 23:36.514
SHE'S ACTING LIKE EVERYTHING'S
FINE, SO WHO KNOWS? MAYBE IT IS.

23:36.516 --> 23:40.084
OR MAYBE WE
HAVE TO RAISE ANOTHER KID.

23:40.086 --> 23:41.619
OH,
CHANGED MY MIND.

23:41.621 --> 23:45.122
I DON'T WANT TO KNOW.
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:47.960 --> 23:49.994
WE'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

23:49.996 --> 23:52.062
WE ALWAYS DO.

23:53.966 --> 23:57.501
WHEN IT COMES TO THE KIDS, WE
ALMOST KNOW WHAT WE'RE DOING.

23:57.503 --> 23:59.003
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

23:59.005 --> 24:00.704
MM.

24:00.706 --> 24:03.541
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:03.543 --> 24:05.976
[ SIGHS ]

24:05.978 --> 24:09.980
WELL, I GUESS THERE'S NO POINT
IN WORRYING UNTIL WE KNOW.

24:09.982 --> 24:11.232
I ALMOST FORGOT --

24:11.233 --> 24:12.483
UH, VANESSA INVITED US
TO A DINNER PARTY TONIGHT.

24:12.485 --> 24:15.119
SHE HELPED NATALIE
LIE TO US.

24:15.121 --> 24:17.021
DINNER PARTY'S
NOT GONNA FIX THAT.

24:17.023 --> 24:19.557
JOE AND VANESSA ARE THE ONLY
ONES WHO HAVE SUPPORTED US

24:19.559 --> 24:21.125
SINCE THIS WHOLE NIGHTMARE
STARTED.

24:21.127 --> 24:24.495
I'LL GET OVER IT,
BUT NOT BY TONIGHT, NO.

24:24.497 --> 24:26.030
SORRY.

24:38.177 --> 24:40.177
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

24:52.124 --> 24:54.658
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:54.660 --> 24:57.027
THE ONE TIME
I'M NOT PROCRASTINATING.

24:57.029 --> 25:00.865
OH, I'M SORRY, MAN.
NO, NO,
IT'S -- IT'S FINE.

25:02.268 --> 25:05.970
HOW GOOD ARE YOU AT FINDING OUT
STUFF ABOUT PEOPLE?

25:05.972 --> 25:07.938
UH, WHAT DO YOU
WANT TO KNOW?

25:07.940 --> 25:10.774
NO, I MEAN, IF YOU COULD JUST
GIVE ME SOME POINTERS AND --

25:10.776 --> 25:13.077
PROBABLY EASIER
IF I JUST DID IT.

25:15.114 --> 25:18.949
THERE'S THIS DOCTOR,
JOSEPH RAWLINGS,

25:18.951 --> 25:22.286
BUT HE CHANGED HIS NAME IN 2007
WHEN HE CAME HERE FROM ENGLAND.

25:22.288 --> 25:23.854
NOW IT'S RICHARDSON.

25:23.856 --> 25:26.123
SO, WHAT ARE YOU
LOOKING FOR?

25:26.125 --> 25:28.792
I WANT TO FIND OUT
ABOUT A FAMILY COURT HEARING

25:28.794 --> 25:31.795
IN MANCHESTER,
BUT IT'S SEALED.

25:31.797 --> 25:34.798
OH, WELL, UH,
NOT EVEN PROSECUTORS

25:34.800 --> 25:36.267
CAN UNTIE TAPE
THAT RED.

25:36.269 --> 25:37.568
WHAT DID HE DO?

25:37.570 --> 25:39.887
I'M NOT SURE.

25:39.888 --> 25:42.205
HE AND HIS WIFE WERE INVOLVED IN
SOME KIND OF SEXUAL MISCONDUCT.

25:42.208 --> 25:44.575
I KNOW HE WAS FIRED
BECAUSE OF IT.

25:44.577 --> 25:47.745
THEN HE CHANGED HIS NAME,
HE MOVED HERE, AND...

25:47.747 --> 25:49.647
HE WAS TOM MURPHY'S
DOCTOR.

25:49.649 --> 25:53.984
OH. [ SIGHS ]

25:53.986 --> 25:56.787
YOU WANT TO FIND OUT
IF HE DID ANYTHING TO YOUR KID.

25:58.257 --> 26:00.991
THE COURT HEARING
MAY BE SEALED,

26:00.993 --> 26:03.561
BUT MEDICAL-BOARD HEARINGS
AREN'T.

26:03.563 --> 26:06.730
NOW, IT WON'T BE EASY --
DOCTORS PROTECT EACH OTHER.

26:06.732 --> 26:09.700
BUT, UM...

26:09.702 --> 26:10.935
LET ME SEE
WHAT I CAN DIG UP.

26:10.937 --> 26:13.671
ARE YOU SURE?

26:13.673 --> 26:15.839
YEAH, NO,
IT'S NO TROUBLE AT ALL.

26:15.841 --> 26:16.974
LISTEN...

26:16.976 --> 26:19.009
HOW WELL
DO YOU KNOW THIS GUY?

26:19.011 --> 26:20.744
HE'S A NEIGHBOR.

26:20.746 --> 26:22.646
TWO WEEKS AGO, I WOULD HAVE
CALLED HIM A FRIEND.

26:22.648 --> 26:24.181
SO YOU'VE BEEN
INSIDE HIS HOUSE?

26:24.183 --> 26:25.349
SURE.

26:25.351 --> 26:26.850
HERE'S THE THING --

26:26.852 --> 26:28.852
IF HE HAS A HISTORY
OF SEX WITH KIDS,

26:28.854 --> 26:30.354
THEN HE'S PROBABLY
COLLECTED STUFF,

26:30.356 --> 26:34.158
YOU KNOW, UM, LOCKS OF HAIR,
SMALL TOYS, CLOTHES --

26:34.160 --> 26:36.860
SOME KIND OF TROPHY.

26:36.862 --> 26:39.163
CHRISTY, IT'S ME.

26:39.165 --> 26:41.332
I CHANGED MY MIND
ABOUT DINNER.

26:41.334 --> 26:43.000
I'LL BE HOME SOON.

26:43.002 --> 26:44.234
[ BEEP ]

26:52.845 --> 26:55.012
STUNNING.

26:55.014 --> 26:57.014
JUST GIVE ME
10 MINUTES.

26:57.016 --> 26:58.015
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

26:58.017 --> 27:00.951
[ WATER RUNNING ]

27:00.953 --> 27:02.019
HMM.

27:03.889 --> 27:06.056
[ LAUGHTER ]
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

27:06.058 --> 27:08.892
EVERYONE,
BEN AND CHRISTY.

27:08.894 --> 27:10.194
HEY!

27:10.196 --> 27:11.362
UH, WE'RE ON THE RED.
IS THAT OKAY?

27:11.364 --> 27:13.097
YEAH, IT'S GREAT.

27:13.098 --> 27:14.831
UH, JULIE AND BRYAN,
RAQUEL AND ANDREW.

27:14.834 --> 27:15.933
All: HI.

27:15.935 --> 27:18.135
GOOD TO MEET YOU, BEN.
YOU TOO.

27:18.137 --> 27:20.204
TERRIBLE WHAT THE, UH,
PRESS IS DOING TO YOU.

27:20.206 --> 27:22.406
HMM.
AH.
OH, THEY THRIVE
ON WITCH-HUNTS.

27:22.408 --> 27:24.842
BRYAN, YOU COULD
AT LEAST RAMP UP.

27:24.844 --> 27:26.377
TALK ABOUT
THIS UNSEASONABLE WEATHER.

27:26.379 --> 27:28.179
IT'S OKAY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:28.180 --> 27:29.980
IT'S BETTER THAN THE USUAL
STARES AND HUSHED GOSSIP.

27:29.982 --> 27:31.782
THANK YOU.
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:31.784 --> 27:34.885
SO, BEN...

27:34.887 --> 27:36.754
HOW ABOUT
THIS HEAT WAVE?

27:36.756 --> 27:39.089
OH! YEAH.
[ LAUGHTER ]

27:39.091 --> 27:40.257
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

27:40.259 --> 27:42.126
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

27:42.128 --> 27:44.294
[ LAUGHTER ]

27:51.437 --> 27:53.837
Andrew:
WE'VE BEEN TOGETHER TWO YEARS.

27:53.839 --> 27:55.139
IT JUST FEELS LIKE 30.

27:55.141 --> 27:57.207
Raquel: EASY.

27:57.209 --> 27:59.743
Bryan: CAN'T BE 30.
UH, RAQUEL'S NOT OLD ENOUGH.

27:59.745 --> 28:00.978
Julie: BRYAN!

28:00.980 --> 28:02.012
[ LAUGHTER ]

28:05.751 --> 28:09.053
Andrew: SO, BEN, HOW LONG
HAVE YOU TWO BEEN TOGETHER?

28:09.055 --> 28:10.220
20 YEARS.

28:10.222 --> 28:12.856
WOW. HOW DID YOU MEET?
OH.

28:12.858 --> 28:14.942
YOU WANT TO TELL IT?

28:14.943 --> 28:17.027
YOU ALWAYS SAY I MESS IT UP,
SO YOU TELL IT.

28:17.029 --> 28:18.445
OH, COME ON.
[ LAUGHTER ]

28:18.446 --> 28:19.862
OKAY, FINE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:19.865 --> 28:22.900
FRESHMAN YEAR, I, UH --
I FOUND THIS RESTAURANT

28:22.902 --> 28:26.203
THAT HAD A MEAL THAT WAS
REALLY GREAT FOR UNDER 20 BUCKS,

28:26.205 --> 28:29.006
AND THERE WAS THIS WAITER
THAT KEPT SCREWING UP MY ORDER.

28:29.008 --> 28:31.942
I WASN'T SCREWING UP.
I WAS STALLING.

28:31.944 --> 28:33.343
OH, YOU HAD TO WORK UP
THE NERVE TO ASK ME OUT.

28:33.345 --> 28:35.813
I WENT BACK FOUR TIMES.

28:35.815 --> 28:37.848
[ LAUGHTER ]
PERSISTENT -- I LIKE IT.

28:38.951 --> 28:41.051
WELL...
[ LAUGHTER ]

28:41.053 --> 28:44.354
WOULD YOU EXCUSE ME?

28:44.356 --> 28:45.706
[ LAUGHTER ]

28:45.707 --> 28:47.057
MM, UPSTAIRS
ON THE LEFT-HAND SIDE.

28:47.059 --> 28:48.459
I MEAN...

28:48.461 --> 28:49.960
Woman: WE COULDN'T
HAVE INVENTED THIS STORY.

28:49.962 --> 28:53.997
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

28:53.999 --> 28:56.033
WOW!

28:56.035 --> 28:58.802
YEAH.

28:58.804 --> 29:01.939
[ CONVERSATION, LAUGHTER
CONTINUE IN DISTANCE ]

29:24.830 --> 29:26.396
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

29:26.398 --> 29:29.299
[ LAUGHTER ]

29:44.283 --> 29:47.017
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

29:49.088 --> 29:50.420
[ DRAWER CLOSES ]

29:50.422 --> 29:52.923
WHY DID YOU AND VANESSA
LEAVE ENGLAND?

29:52.925 --> 29:54.792
THAT'S AN ODD QUESTION

29:54.794 --> 29:56.527
FOR SOMEONE WHO'S
RIFLING THROUGH MY DESK.

29:56.529 --> 29:59.229
WHY DID YOU
CHANGE YOUR NAME?

29:59.231 --> 30:00.397
LEAVE.

30:00.399 --> 30:01.932
NOT UNTIL
I GET ANSWERS.

30:01.934 --> 30:03.400
HAVE YOU LOST
YOUR MIND?!

30:03.402 --> 30:06.303
YOU WERE FIRED
FOR SEXUAL MISCONDUCT.

30:06.305 --> 30:08.038
YOU'RE MY KIDS' DOCTOR.

30:08.040 --> 30:10.274
WHAT DID YOU DO,
AND WHAT ARE YOU RUNNING FROM?

30:10.276 --> 30:12.943
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE.

30:12.945 --> 30:15.045
WHY DID YOU LOSE CUSTODY
OF YOUR SON?

30:15.047 --> 30:16.980
I SAW THE PICTURES
AND THE BRUISES.

30:16.982 --> 30:19.850
[ GASPS ]
IF YOU KEPT QUIET, VANESSA,
YOU'RE NO BETTER!

30:19.852 --> 30:20.951
THAT WAS YOUR SON!

30:20.953 --> 30:22.886
BEN, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?!

30:22.888 --> 30:24.822
WHAT HAPPENED
TO MALCOLM?

30:24.824 --> 30:28.125
I LOVED MY SON,
AND I NEVER HURT HIM!

30:28.127 --> 30:29.526
WHAT ABOUT TOM?

30:29.528 --> 30:31.178
DID YOU TOUCH HIM,

30:31.179 --> 30:32.829
AND HE THREATENED TO TELL
SO YOU HAD TO BEAT HIM?!

30:32.832 --> 30:36.466
BEN!
HOW DARE YOU?

30:36.468 --> 30:38.101
I NEVER TOUCHED TOM.

30:38.103 --> 30:39.603
YOU'RE A LIAR.

30:39.605 --> 30:41.438
YOU MURDERED MY SON,

30:41.440 --> 30:44.408
AND YOU USED
MY FLASHLIGHT TO DO IT!

30:45.911 --> 30:47.578
[ DOOR OPENS ]
I'M -- I'M SO SORRY!

30:50.416 --> 30:51.482
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

30:51.483 --> 30:52.549
[ DOOR OPENS, SLAMS ]
[ INDISTINCT WHISPERING ]

30:57.289 --> 30:59.957
FIRST SCOTT KILLED TOM,
NOW JOE DID IT!

30:59.959 --> 31:01.525
YOU'RE ACTING
LIKE A LUNATIC, BEN!

31:01.527 --> 31:03.744
YOU DON'T HAVE ALL THE FACTS!
YOU DON'T KNOW!

31:03.745 --> 31:05.962
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?!
CHRISTY, YOU OKAY?

31:05.965 --> 31:07.931
I'M FINE!
STAY OUT OF IT, ELAINE!

31:07.933 --> 31:10.334
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

31:16.008 --> 31:18.976
[ BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY ]

31:18.978 --> 31:20.310
THEY HAD A SON...
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

31:20.312 --> 31:21.979
...WHO DIED.

31:21.981 --> 31:24.481
I SAW THE PICTURES.
HE WAS BEATEN AND BRUISED.

31:24.483 --> 31:26.016
I STILL SOUND CRAZY?

31:26.018 --> 31:27.317
NO, YOU SOUND LIKE
THE SAME LYING SON OF A BITCH

31:27.319 --> 31:29.236
WHO NEVER TELLS ME
WHAT I NEED TO KNOW.

31:29.237 --> 31:31.154
YOU DON'T<i> WANT</i> TO KNOW!
THAT --
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

31:40.532 --> 31:42.065
UM...

31:42.067 --> 31:43.500
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

31:43.502 --> 31:46.503
H-HE BRUISED EASILY,

31:46.505 --> 31:49.139
BUT WE -- WE DIDN'T
KNOW ANYTHING WAS WRONG.

31:49.141 --> 31:51.909
HE DIDN'T
COMPLAIN ONCE.

31:51.911 --> 31:54.044
YOUR HUSBAND'S A DOCTOR,
VANESSA.

31:54.046 --> 31:56.680
YEAH, SOMETIMES
DOCTORS GET IT WRONG.

31:56.682 --> 31:58.916
HE HAD UNDIAGNOSED
HEMOPHILIA.

31:58.918 --> 32:02.986
HE'D BEEN SLOWLY BLEEDING
INTERNALLY FOR MONTHS.

32:02.988 --> 32:04.988
THE DOCTOR
AT THE HOSPITAL,

32:04.990 --> 32:08.592
HE -- HE THOUGHT WE HAD ABUSED
HIM, JUST LIKE YOU, AND...

32:08.594 --> 32:12.029
HE CALLED THE POLICE.

32:12.031 --> 32:14.364
THEY JUST TOOK HIM!

32:14.366 --> 32:16.133
WHY DIDN'T YOU
GET HIM BACK?

32:16.135 --> 32:19.069
NO ONE CHANGES THEIR MIND
ONCE THEY THINK YOU'RE GUILTY.

32:19.071 --> 32:24.641
THEY PLACED MALCOLM IN A GROUP
HOME TILL WE COULD SORT IT OUT.

32:24.643 --> 32:28.946
THE MAN IN CHARGE...
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

32:28.948 --> 32:32.516
...HE --
HE BEAT HIM REPEATEDLY.

32:32.518 --> 32:35.686
THE PHOTO YOU SAW
WAS EVIDENCE THAT WE GATHERED

32:35.688 --> 32:38.121
TO TRY AND GET
OUR SON BACK...

32:39.692 --> 32:42.025
...BUT WE
WERE TOO LATE.

32:42.027 --> 32:47.164
HE -- HE DIED TWO WEEKS
BEFORE THE HEARING.

32:49.034 --> 32:50.734
VANESSA, I AM SO SORRY.

32:50.736 --> 32:52.402
Ben: WAIT.
YOU KNOW WHO KILLED YOUR SON.

32:52.404 --> 32:53.971
I WANT TO KNOW
WHO KILLED MINE.

32:53.973 --> 32:56.273
WELL, IT WASN'T ME,
AND IT WASN'T JOE.

32:56.275 --> 32:57.708
HE'S A GOOD MAN.

32:57.710 --> 32:59.209
THEN WHY
DID HE LOSE HIS JOB?

32:59.211 --> 33:01.144
WHAT WAS
THE SEXUAL MISCONDUCT?

33:01.146 --> 33:04.982
THAT HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH TOM'S MURDER.

33:04.984 --> 33:06.183
I PROMISE YOU.

33:06.185 --> 33:09.720
IT'S JUST ME ASKING NOW,
VANESSA.

33:09.722 --> 33:11.989
SOON,
IT'LL BE THE COPS.

33:31.643 --> 33:33.610
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

33:39.551 --> 33:41.051
NATALIE.

33:41.053 --> 33:42.486
WE EAT HERE.

33:42.488 --> 33:45.389
IT SAYS "MINUS."
THAT'S GOOD, RIGHT?

33:45.391 --> 33:48.125
SO, WE'RE DONE NOW?
NO.

33:48.127 --> 33:49.793
WE STILL
HAVE PLENTY TO SAY.

33:49.795 --> 33:53.130
"DO AS I SAY, NOT AS I DO" --
GOT IT.

33:53.132 --> 33:54.665
WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

33:54.666 --> 33:56.199
MOM WAS KNOCKED UP
WHEN YOU GOT MARRIED

33:56.201 --> 33:58.101
AND NOT MUCH OLDER THAN ME.
I WAS READY.

33:58.103 --> 33:59.770
I'M GOING TO COLLEGE
IN A YEAR!

33:59.772 --> 34:01.171
SO?

34:01.173 --> 34:02.539
WHAT DID YOU PLAN TO DO
IF YOU WERE PREGNANT?

34:02.541 --> 34:05.542
DO YOU EVEN THINK
ABOUT BIRTH CONTROL?

34:05.544 --> 34:08.378
I DON'T WANT YOU TO MAKE
THE SAME MISTAKE I DID.

34:08.380 --> 34:10.080
AND WHICH MISTAKE
WAS THAT --

34:10.082 --> 34:11.515
HAVING ME
OR MARRYING DAD?

34:12.751 --> 34:15.085
NEITHER OF THOSE DECISIONS
WAS A MISTAKE.

34:15.087 --> 34:17.254
NATALIE, YOU'RE ANGRY,

34:17.256 --> 34:19.523
BUT YOU HAVE NO RIGHT TO BLAME
YOUR MOTHER FOR ANYTHING.

34:19.525 --> 34:21.258
BUT I CAN BLAME YOU.

34:21.260 --> 34:24.761
YEAH, YOU CAN.

34:24.763 --> 34:27.364
YOU CAN.
I DID THIS TO OUR FAMILY.

34:27.366 --> 34:29.699
YOU HAD HELP.

34:29.701 --> 34:30.801
WHAT DID YOU DO,
MOM?

34:30.803 --> 34:32.836
NOTHING.
SHE DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

34:32.838 --> 34:34.438
THIS IS ON ME, ABBY.

34:34.440 --> 34:37.207
ALL OF IT.

34:37.209 --> 34:38.708
BUT HERE'S THE THING,
NAT --

34:38.710 --> 34:42.546
YOU CAN SCREAM AND SLAM YOUR
DOOR AND FIGHT ALL YOU WANT,

34:42.548 --> 34:44.548
BUT I'M GONNA STAY
IN YOUR FACE.

34:44.550 --> 34:45.849
AND I'LL CONTINUE
TO MAKE RULES,

34:45.851 --> 34:48.618
AND I'LL CONTINUE TO
EMBARRASS YOU IN PUBLIC...

34:48.620 --> 34:52.422
BECAUSE I CARE.

34:52.424 --> 34:55.125
AND I'D DO ANYTHING
TO PROTECT YOU,

34:55.127 --> 34:57.394
EVEN IF IT'S
FROM YOURSELF.

35:01.300 --> 35:02.632
OKAY.

35:02.634 --> 35:04.534
OKAY.

35:17.382 --> 35:19.549
DAVE
DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

35:19.551 --> 35:23.720
AFTER COOPER'S PARTY, I WAS
DRUNK AND CRYING AND MAD AT YOU,

35:23.722 --> 35:25.555
SO DAVE
GAVE ME A HUG.

35:27.126 --> 35:30.227
SERIOUSLY, HE'S LIKE
MY UNCLE -- GROSS.

35:30.229 --> 35:31.595
MM.

35:45.144 --> 35:47.144
Fenton:
YOU WERE RIGHT --

35:47.146 --> 35:50.614
DEFINITELY SOMETHING HINKY
ABOUT THE RICHARDSONS.

35:50.616 --> 35:52.782
WHAT DID YOU FIND OUT?

35:52.784 --> 35:55.418
WELL, THEIR SON, MALCOLM,
HAD HEMOPHILIA,

35:55.420 --> 35:57.420
AND WHEN THE HOSPITAL
RAN THE BLOOD,

35:57.422 --> 35:59.589
THEY FOUND OUT
THAT MOM AND DAD

35:59.591 --> 36:02.492
BOTH HAD THE SAME
MITOCHONDRIAL DNA.

36:02.494 --> 36:04.695
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

36:04.696 --> 36:06.897
JOE AND VANESSA
HAD THE SAME MOTHER.

36:06.899 --> 36:09.566
THEY'RE
BROTHER AND SISTER?

36:09.568 --> 36:11.801
HALF, BUT YES.

36:11.803 --> 36:14.838
TURNS OUT HEMOPHILIA IS
A NASTY BY-PRODUCT OF INCEST.

36:14.840 --> 36:17.340
OF COURSE, THE RICHARDSONS --
OR SHOULD I SAY RAWLINGS --

36:17.342 --> 36:18.808
CLAIMED THEY DIDN'T KNOW
THAT THEY WERE RELATED.

36:18.810 --> 36:22.579
HELL OF A JUICY STORY,
DON'T YOU THINK?

36:24.483 --> 36:26.816
YOU'RE A REPORTER?

36:26.818 --> 36:29.653
WHICH MAKES YOU
MY UNNAMED SOURCE.

36:29.655 --> 36:31.421
CARE TO COMMENT?

36:38.330 --> 36:39.863
YOU CAN'T PRINT THAT.

36:39.865 --> 36:41.831
SURE I CAN.

36:41.833 --> 36:43.967
BUT YOU JUST SAID THEY HAVE
NOTHING TO DO WITH TOM'S MURDER.

36:43.969 --> 36:46.836
WELL, THAT DOESN'T MATTER.
IT'S SO EASY TO SPIN.

36:46.838 --> 36:48.738
SEXUAL DEVIANCE
TO CHILD KILLER --

36:48.740 --> 36:50.073
NOT A HUGE LEAP.

36:50.074 --> 36:51.407
YOU MADE IT,
AND SO WILL THE PUBLIC.

36:51.410 --> 36:54.244
[ Chuckling ] BEN, BEN,
THIS COULD HELP YOU --

36:54.246 --> 36:57.480
BOTCH THE INVESTIGATION,
CORNELL -- SHE GETS A BLACK EYE.

36:57.482 --> 37:00.617
NO, I'M NOT GONNA RUIN
THEIR LIVES TO SAVE MINE!

37:03.455 --> 37:05.922
OKAY.

37:05.924 --> 37:07.924
I COULD BE CONVINCED
NOT TO RUN THE STORY

37:07.926 --> 37:11.294
IF I HAD A BETTER ONE.

37:11.296 --> 37:13.230
LIKE YOUR EXCLUSIVE.

37:13.232 --> 37:15.398
THERE IS NO STORY.
I'M NOT GUILTY.

37:15.400 --> 37:16.900
THERE'S ALWAYS A STORY.

37:16.902 --> 37:19.436
IT JUST DEPENDS IF YOU
WANT TO LOOK GOOD OR BAD.

37:19.438 --> 37:21.438
I MEAN,
YOU TOOK A POLYGRAPH.

37:21.440 --> 37:23.940
NOW, I'M GUESSING
IF YOU PASSED,

37:23.942 --> 37:26.409
YOU WOULD HAVE RELEASED
THE RESULTS TO THE PRESS.

37:26.411 --> 37:28.745
WHY ARE YOU
DOING THIS TO ME?

37:28.747 --> 37:31.915
IT'S NOT ABOUT YOU.
YOU'RE JUST A CASUALTY OF WAR.

37:35.387 --> 37:38.855
JOE, VANESSA,
THERE'S A REPORTER.

37:38.857 --> 37:41.891
HE FOUND OUT
ABOUT YOUR STORY.

37:41.893 --> 37:44.894
[ SIGHS ]
AND I'M SORRY.

37:46.965 --> 37:49.633
I'M SORRY.

37:49.635 --> 37:51.701
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

37:54.973 --> 37:57.674
Man:
YOU WANT TO TALK TO US TODAY?

37:57.676 --> 37:59.643
[ SHOUTING CONTINUES ]

37:59.645 --> 38:00.844
Man #2:
WHAT'S THE SITUATION?

38:00.846 --> 38:02.712
Man #3: BEN!
Man #4: BEN!

38:02.714 --> 38:04.147
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]
Woman: MR. CRAWFORD,

38:04.148 --> 38:05.581
WHAT IS YOUR CONNECTION
TO THE RICHARDSONS?

38:05.584 --> 38:06.750
MR. CRAWFORD?

38:06.752 --> 38:08.551
Man: COME ON!

38:08.553 --> 38:10.620
[ DOOR OPENS ]

38:16.995 --> 38:20.697
EXCUSE ME. I'LL BE
OUT OF YOUR HAIR IN A
MINUTE,<i> IF</i> THAT'S COOL.

38:20.699 --> 38:22.999
DUDE, IS THERE ANY WAY
I CAN GET YOU TO FORGIVE ME?

38:23.001 --> 38:24.501
[ SIGHS ]

38:24.503 --> 38:27.304
MORE.

38:27.306 --> 38:30.807
I'VE BEEN A...
TOTAL ASS.

38:30.809 --> 38:32.809
GO ON.
[ SIGHS ]

38:32.811 --> 38:35.512
I SWEAR TO GOD,
IF THERE'S ANYTHING I CAN DO,

38:35.514 --> 38:37.347
YEAH...
...ANYTHING
I CAN GET YOU...

38:37.349 --> 38:38.415
...I MADE A LIST.

38:40.319 --> 38:41.384
OKAY.

38:44.523 --> 38:46.823
SERIOUSLY? HOW MANY
DIFFERENT WAYS DO I DIE?

38:46.825 --> 38:48.091
SEVERAL.

38:48.093 --> 38:49.959
IS THAT A HATCHET?

38:49.961 --> 38:52.829
IT'S A VIKING BATTLE AX,
BEN.

38:52.831 --> 38:55.865
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S A LONG LIST.

38:55.867 --> 38:58.101
SO,
READ THE TOP FOUR.

38:58.103 --> 39:00.403
NUMBER ONE, BEER.

39:00.405 --> 39:02.772
NUMBER TWO, BEER.
YEAH.

39:02.774 --> 39:04.841
NUMBER --
KEEP READING.

39:06.411 --> 39:08.912
IT'S ALL BEER.
[ CHUCKLES ] I'M KIDDING.

39:08.914 --> 39:11.815
AND I DIDN'T SAY SQUAT
TO CORNELL, OKAY?

39:11.817 --> 39:15.085
SHE WAS LIKE, "SPILL IT,"
AND I WAS LIKE, "NAW, PIG."

39:15.087 --> 39:18.421
[ Chuckling ] ACTUALLY, IT
DIDN'T -- DIDN'T GO DOWN LIKE
THAT AT ALL, BUT, UH...

39:18.423 --> 39:22.425
OH, SHE WANTED TO KNOW
IF YOU HAD A BLUE JACKET.

39:22.427 --> 39:23.727
WOMAN'S AN OYSTER,

39:23.729 --> 39:26.629
BUT I'M THINKING THAT THE KILLER
HAD A BLUE JACKET.

39:26.631 --> 39:28.898
THANKS.
YEAH.

39:28.900 --> 39:32.602
MAN, I KNOW
I'VE BEEN ACTING CRAZY.

39:32.604 --> 39:33.737
YEAH.

39:33.739 --> 39:35.572
BUT I STILL
CAN'T REMEMBER THAT NIGHT.

39:35.574 --> 39:39.109
CORNELL'S ALL OVER ME.
MAYBE I'M JUST PARANOID.

39:39.111 --> 39:43.646
NO, MAN, SHE -- SHE DEFINITELY
HAS WOOD FOR YOU, BUT...

39:43.648 --> 39:45.815
I GOT YOUR BACK, OKAY?

39:45.817 --> 39:46.916
REMEMBER THAT.

39:46.918 --> 39:48.785
YOU DON'T HAVE TO GO.

39:48.787 --> 39:52.088
YEAH, I DO.
I GOT A STUDIO.

39:53.959 --> 39:56.025
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

39:58.797 --> 40:01.464
I'M READY FOR MY CLOSE-UP,
PARASITES!

40:01.466 --> 40:03.500
WHERE DO YOU WANT ME -- HERE?
Woman: YEAH.

40:03.502 --> 40:05.568
RIGHT HERE? YOU GOT ME?
GREAT.

40:05.570 --> 40:07.070
BACK OFF!

40:10.175 --> 40:12.409
[ CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

40:12.411 --> 40:13.943
[ CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING ]

40:19.851 --> 40:21.918
[ HORN HONKS ]

40:37.736 --> 40:39.869
THEY'RE GONE,
YOU KNOW?

40:39.871 --> 40:42.205
I WASN'T
TRYING TO HURT THEM.

40:42.207 --> 40:44.574
YET YOU DID.

40:44.576 --> 40:47.544
I WAS INTRIGUED BY THE CHOICE
OF WORDS YOU USED, THOUGH.

40:47.546 --> 40:49.712
WITH THE DOCTOR.

40:49.714 --> 40:53.917
"YOU MURDERED MY SON, AND YOU
USED MY FLASHLIGHT TO DO IT."

40:53.919 --> 40:57.487
YOU CAME ALL THIS WAY
TO SAY THAT?

40:57.489 --> 41:01.124
DID YOU CALL JESS MURPHY
THE NIGHT TOM WAS KILLED?

41:01.126 --> 41:02.826
NO.

41:02.828 --> 41:04.494
YOU SURE?
ABSOLUTELY.

41:04.496 --> 41:07.597
I ONLY ASK AGAIN

41:07.598 --> 41:10.699
BECAUSE YOUR MEMORY SEEMS TO BE
SO CONVENIENTLY UNRELIABLE.

41:10.702 --> 41:14.704
DO YOU KNOW
A-A SARAH JENKINS?

41:14.706 --> 41:15.839
NO.

41:15.841 --> 41:17.507
WELL, JESS AND SARAH

41:17.509 --> 41:19.976
SHARE ALMOST THE SAME
TELEPHONE NUMBER.

41:19.978 --> 41:21.845
WHAT DOES THAT
HAVE TO DO WITH ME?

41:21.847 --> 41:24.013
WELL, I PULLED
YOUR CELLPHONE RECORDS,

41:24.015 --> 41:27.016
AND ON SARAH JENKINS' VOICEMAIL
THE NIGHT TOM WAS MURDERED...

41:27.018 --> 41:27.884
[ BEEP ]

41:27.886 --> 41:30.019
...YOU LEFT THIS MESSAGE.

41:30.021 --> 41:31.554
[<i> Indistinct conversations</i> ]

41:31.556 --> 41:35.024
BEN:<i> [ Slurring ]</i>
<i> Jess, it's me, Ben.</i>

41:35.026 --> 41:38.628
<i> Listen, I-I don't know</i>
<i> what's gonna happen tomorrow.</i>

41:38.630 --> 41:41.097
<i> I just wanted --</i>
<i> I just wanted to say...</i>

41:41.099 --> 41:43.032
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

41:44.135 --> 41:47.504
CAN YOU EXPLAIN THAT,
MR. CRAWFORD?
